models.name: Brushed Quad Frame
models.description:
Brushed quad frame for this controller:

https://www.banggood.com/Micro-F3-Flight-Controller-Board-Buited-In-DSM-FLYSKY-FRSKY-Receiver-For-Eachine-E010S-p-1131611.html

and these motors:

https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00SKVZMU4/ref=oh_aui_search_detailpage?ie=UTF8&psc=1

The motors should be friction fit. You may wish to wrap a small section of masking tape around the can of the motor (perhaps 5mm wide) to improve the friction fit.

Note you will need to mount the controller "upside down" and configure the controller software accordingly.

models.name: Lambretta Service Man
models.description:
This is a 3D-model of the Lambretta Service Man, you can choose between two different files, one with an engraved lettering(v4) and one with a put-on lettering(v3).

It may looks better if you print the layers in different colours, then you have to print every colour for a height of 2mm, if you have v3 u can use 3 colours, if you have v4 you can use 2 colours.

Note: I have not added any support nor have I printed it so I don't know how well it works. Feel free to experiment.  

Edit: I made an "Easy Print" table with all pieces, But it's very much a WIP so use at your own risk. I also released a 123dx file unmerged for use in 123 Design.
models.instructions: I have no idea how to print this. In worst case you might have to slice him up in 100 pieces and glue him back together.

models.name: Miniature Bedroom Accessories
models.description:
Medieval Miniature Bedroom Accessories - Folding Screen, Wash Basin, and Breakfast Tray. Folding screens are designed to snap into each other, but care must be taken when removing the supports for the pins. The pins are purposely oversized and must be sanded to fit the receivers. Also the design is set to not fully become straight. This can be fixed by sanding the inboard side of the pin more than the outer. I have snapped the pins off before and then superglued them back and it worked fine. Picture for folding screen is obviously your own preference. I suggest snapping the pieces together and then cutting each piece across the folding screens to get your design.
Other bedroom items of canopy bed, pillows and chest of drawers can be found here.
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2773754
